NORTHROP GRUMMAN CORP., Los Angeles, said it won a $171 million contract from the Navy for an amphibious assault ship.

FRONTLINE COMMUNICATIONS CORP., Pearl River, N.Y., an Internet service provider, agreed to be bought by Shecom Corp., Yorba Linda, Calif., a seller of computers, in a stock swap. Terms were not disclosed.

NOVEON INTERNATIONAL INC., Cleveland, a maker of specialty materials, said it would seek to raise about $345 million through an initial public offering.

WELLS FARGO & CO., San Francisco, agreed to buy Nelson Capital Management, Palo Alto, Calif., an investment advisory company. Terms were not disclosed.